Write a python program to find whether two arrays are same using one-dimensional arrays.

n = int(input("Enter how many values you want to read: "))
print("For array 'a':")
a = [int(input("Enter the value of a[{}]: ".format(i))) for i in range(n)]
print("For array 'b':")
b = [int(input("Enter the value of b[{}]: ".format(i))) for i in range(n)]
if a == b:
    print("Both arrays are equal")
else:
    print("Both arrays are not equal")
